51 mm diam, 51 mm thick. Absolute detector efficiency
was determined by measuring D-T neutrons at 14.9 MeV
and neutron scattered by hydrogen at energies 11.1,
6.4, 3.1 MeV. Relative detector efficiency was deter-
mined by measuring spontaneous fission neutron from
350 keV deuteron beam borbarding tritium target
.Corrections were made for (i) attenuation of source
neutrons in sample, (ii) multiple scattering in sample
(iii) neutrons below 10 MeV, (iv) attenuation of scat-
tered neutrons travelling the flight path. All calcu-
